{"name": "zpz", "metadata": {"name": "zpz", "version": "0.5.2", "classifiers": ["Intended Audience :: Developers", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["boltons"], "summary": "Python utilities.", "upload_time": 1733600798}, "documentation": ["Python Utilities\n================\n\nThis repo collects some small Python utilities that I have created (or collected) in practice,\nand organizes them as a package named `zpz`.\n\nThese utilities are not \"one-off\" experiments; they are really useful code.\nHowever, they do not form a coherent set of utilities for a particular application domain.\nIt's reasonable to consider it to be mainly for the author's personal conveniences.\nHowever, I also refrain from making arbitrary, unnecessary breaking changes.\nNew releases are made on an as-needed basis.\n\nTo install, do\n\n```\npip install zpz\n```\n\nThere are some optional dependencies for specific modules.\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "zpz.docker", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "zpz.docker.get_host_ip", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Get the IP address of the host machine from within a Docker container."]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "zpz.text", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "zpz.text.isascii", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "text", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "zpz.async_", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "zpz.async_.async_call", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": 