, "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "tzname", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "datetime", "xref": {"fqname": "datetime.datetime", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Get the current `datetime` in the specified timezone.\n\nArgs:\n\n: tzname: the ISO standard timezone name,\n  such as `Africa/Cairo`, `America/Los_Angeles`.\n"]}, {"name": "zpz.datetime.isoformatnow", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["This function creates a timestamp string with fixed format like\n\n    '2020-08-22T08:09:13.401346+00:00'\n\nThe returned string has fixed length. The microseconds section\nalways takes 6 digits, even if they are all zeros.\n\nStrings created by this function can be compared to\ndetermine time order. There is no need to parse the string\ninto `datetime` objects.\n\nThe returned string is often written as a timestamp file, like\n\n    open(file_name, 'w').write(make_timestamp())\n\nAnother way to make a fixed-length datetime str is to use\n`datetime.strftime('%Y%m%d%H%M%S.%f')`."]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "zpz.profile", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "zpz.profile.profiled", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "top", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "sort_by", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "prof_file", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "", "xref": null, "params": [{"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Print out profiling info for a test function,\nand optionally dump the profile result in specified file\nfor later inspection.\n\nArgs:\n\n: top: number of top items to print.\n  sort_by: list of sort keys for print-out, if not `None`.\n\n  > If `None` (the default), a default list of sort keys are used.\n  > If `[]`, no print-out.\n\n  prof_file: file name for a dump of the profile.\n\n  : Use `snakeviz` to view the content of this file later.\n    If `None`, a default file name is used.\n    If `''`, profile is not saved.\n\nUsage:\n\n```\n@profiled()\ndef func():\n    ...\n\n@profiled(top=20)\ndef func():\n    ...\n```\n\nIn a test function,\n\n```\ndef test_abc():\n    @profiled()\n    def do_it():\n        ...\n\n    do_it()\n```\n"]}, {"name": "zpz.profile.lineprofiled", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "*funcs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "", "xref": null, "params": [{"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["A line-profiling decorator.\n\nArgs:\n    funcs: functions (function objects, not function names)\n        to be line-profiled. If no function is specified,\n        the function being decorated is profiled.\n\nExample:\n\n        @lineprofiled()\n        def myfunc(a, b):\n            g(a)\n            f(b)\n\n        @lineprofiled(g, f)\n        def yourfunc(a, b):\n            x = g(a)\n            y = f(b)\n            s(x, y)"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "zpz.logging", "documentation": ["Configure logging, mainly the format.\n\nA call to the function `config_logger` in a launching script\nis all that is needed to set up the logging format.\nUsually the 'level' argument is the only argument one needs to customize:\n\n```\nconfig_logger(level='info')\n```\n\nDo not call this in library modules. Library modules should have\n\n```\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n```\n\nand then just use `logger` to write logs without concern about formatting,\ndestination of the log message, etc.\n"], "functions": [{"name": "zpz.logging.get_calling_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zpz.logging.formatter", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "with_process_name", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "with_thread_name", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zpz.logging.set_level", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "level", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["In one application, call `set_level` on the top level once.\nDo not set level anywhere else, and do not set level on any handler."]}, {"name": "zpz.logging.health_check", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "handler_name", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zpz.logging.use_console_handler", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zpz.logging._unuse_handler", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"na